which burbles away on your stoves<br>
the peppers are silently plotting <br>
with legumes, tomato's and cloves<br>
at night when you are comfortably sleeping<br>
and lie unaware in your beds<br>
the vegetables plan insurrection<br>
the lettuce are seeking new heads<br>
<br>
It may start with slight indigestion<br>
from underdone turnip cake crumbs<br>
frustration in world in several world leaders<br>
whose rice seems to stick to their gums<br>
in kitchens across every nation<br>
the tiniest things go wrong<br>
the plot of the sentient chili<br>
strikes at Moscow, Rome and Hong Kong<br>
<br>
The casserole, spinach and cheesecake <br>
lend quiet support to the scheme<br>
the nerves of a planet are stretched thin<br>
while tempers slowly start to steam<br>
still none see the grand machinations<br>
now tilting the world balance awry<br>
the stage is now set for final disaster<br>
the chili sits back with a sigh<br>
<br>
Then one day the conflict is started<br>
by Generals whose lunches were odd<br>
the mushrooms rejoice as their brothers<br>
stalk to city to city like gods<br>
<br>
When all the dust and all the clamor are settled<br>
there is not a soul left from the fray<br>
the sentient chili just chuckles<br>
and happily simmers away <p>vita non est vivere sed valere vita est<br>
